    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Compare a and b (lists of strings); return a delta (a generator generating the delta lines) in context diff format. Context diffs are a compact way of showing just the lines that have changed plus a few lines of context. The changes are shown in a before/after style. The number of context lines is set by n which defaults to three. By default, the diff control lines (those with *** or ---) are created with a trailing newline. This is helpful so that inputs created from io.IOBase.readlines() re..."
